events.1862: Master plan for Dakar is drafted by Émile Pinet-Laprade
events.1863: Catholic Apostolic Vicariate of Senegambia established
events.1872: Town becomes part of the commune of Gorée
events.1885: Opening of the Dakar–Saint-Louis railway (163 miles long)
events.1902: Capital of French West Africa moved to Dakar from Saint-Louis
events.1936: Catholic Cathédrale du Souvenir africain de Dakar inaugurated
events.1938: Institut Français d’Afrique Noire and museum founded
events.1973: Council for the Development of Social Science Research in Africa headquartered in Dakar
events.1978: Dakar Rally motor vehicle race begins
events.1989: Musée historique du Sénégal à Gorée opens
events.1996: Municipal administration divided into 19 communes d'arrondissement
events.1999: Festival international du film de quartier de Dakar begins
events.2003: West Africa Democracy Radio begins broadcasting
events.2011: City hosts World Social Forum and ICANN conference
events.2013: June: U.S. President Obama visits city
events.2014: Meeting of the Organisation internationale de la Francophonie held in city
